              "text": "َ قَالَ"
            }
          ]
        },
        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:3:2:2:3",
        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/24/3",
        "text": [
          " عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ : \"إِذَا قَالَ اَلرَّجُلُ لِلرَّجُلِ هَلُمَّ أَحْسِنْ بَيْعَكَ فَقَدْ حَرُمَ عَلَيْهِ اَلرِّبْحُ \"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.3984 - Imam (as) said: \"If a man says to another man, 'Come, I will improve your sale,' then it is forbidden for him to make a profit.\"\n[REFERENCES]\nAl-Kafi, Vol.5 p.152 • Man La Yahduruhu Al-Faqih, Vol.3 p.272 • Tahdhib Al-Ahkam, Vol.7 p.7 • Al-Wafi, Vol.17 p.457 • Wasa'il Al-Shi'ah, Vol.17 p.395 • Bihar Al-Anwar, Vol.100 p.136"
          ]
        }
      }
